This allows positional parameter/primary constructor base records to be incorporated into the positional parameters of the derived record by simply adding those positional parameters to the derived record and linking them through the base argument list.
example:
```
public record Base(int Foo, int Bar);

// note this should be an error as non-records can't inherit from records,
// but if the user performs a series of refactorings down the inheritance hierarchy
// this situation can occur (also in a potential future fix all scenario)
public class Derived : Base
{
    public int Baz { get; init; }
}
```
would turn into:
```
public record Base(int Foo, int Bar);

public record Derived(int Foo, int Bar, int Baz) : Base(Foo, Bar);
```

Also uses `inheritDoc` in xml comments to use the base class field comment (if it exists)

This was originally intended to be a larger PR which would incorporate base initializer calls into constructor refactoring, but that turned out to be not very possible to do unless the base was already a positional record.

